hints_latex:
By the integral test, this sum is convergent if and only if the integral

\begin{align*}
\int_2^\infty \left(\frac{1}{\ln x}\right)^2 \frac{1}{x} \, dx
\end{align*}

converges.

statement_latex:
Determine whether the following series is convergent or divergent.
Remember to justify your answer:

\begin{align*}
\sum_{n=2}^\infty\left(\frac{1}{\ln n}\right)^2\frac{1}{n}
\end{align*}
